Message.MsgText: APMI_SkipPoll=ASPS0018W: Statistics for the middleware agent are not being gathered, because the processing of the previous collection began at {0} and is still in progress.
Message.Explanation: This happens when the local CPUs are overloaded or the process reaches a state of deadlock.
Message.UserResponse: Report the problem to IBM support if CPU overload is unexpected or not present.

Message.MsgText: APMI_XDSYSTEM_REG_ERR=ASPS0022E: Unable to register XdSystem PMI module.
Message.Explanation: Unable to register the XdSystem PMI module.
Message.UserResponse: Review and collect the system log files, and contact IBM support.

Message.MsgText: asps.nopeer=ASPS0011E: Failed to join management overlay network, with name={0}, due to {1}
Message.Explanation: This process failed to join the WebSphere management overlay network, using the given name for itself, because of the given exception
Message.UserResponse: If the problem persists, additional information might be available if you search for the message ID on the following Web sites: WebSphere Application Server Support page: http://www.ibm.com/software/webservers/appserv/was/support/ WebSphere Application Server for z/OS Support page: http://www.ibm.com/software/webservers/appserv/zos_os390/support/ .

If the problem persists, additional information might be available if you search for the message ID on the following Web sites: WebSphere Application Server Support page: http://www.ibm.com/software/webservers/appserv/was/support/ WebSphere Application Server for z/OS Support page: http://www.ibm.com/software/webservers/appserv/zos_os390/support/ .

Message.MsgText: APMI_XDSYSTEM_HW_INFO_WARN=ASPS0023W: The logical partition on which this node resides has a mode of shared, a type of uncapped, but performance collection is not enabled.
Message.Explanation: Performance collection must be enabled for the product to recognize more than the entitled capacity of a logical partition. If performance collection is not enabled, the product will not recognize any additional capacity above the configured entitled capacity.
Message.UserResponse: Enable the Allow Performance Collection feature for the logical partition in the Hardware Management Console.

Message.MsgText: APMI_CoreDumpErr=ASPS0015E: The complete set of states for an unhealthy statistic gathering is: {0}
Message.Explanation: This message provides a detailed list of all statistic gathering states.
Message.UserResponse: Review core group state, and then contact IBM support.

Message.MsgText: APMI_CoreDump=ASPS0014I: The complete set of states for an operational statistics gathering is: {0}
Message.Explanation: This message provides a detailed list of all statistic gathering states.

Message.MsgText: APMI_DropStats=ASPS0019W: Middleware agent statistics {0} are being ignored, because the previous batch began at {1} and is still being processed.
Message.Explanation: This happens when the local CPUs are overloaded or the process reaches a state of deadlock.
Message.UserResponse: Report the problem to IBM support if CPU overload is unexpected or not present.

If the problem persists, additional information might be available if you search for the message ID on the following Web sites: WebSphere Application Server Support page: http://www.ibm.com/software/webservers/appserv/was/support/ WebSphere Application Server for z/OS Support page: http://www.ibm.com/software/webservers/appserv/zos_os390/support/ .

Message.MsgText: APMI_NoDefaultTP=ASPS0017E: ThreadPoolRepository {0} fails to yield a default thread pool.
Message.Explanation: No default thread pool was retrieved from the ThreadPoolRepository.
Message.UserResponse: Define a thread pool for the desired process with a name of Default, a minimum size of 5, and maximum size of 20. In the administrative console, select Servers > All servers > server_name > Thread pools > New to define the thread pool.

Message.MsgText: APMI_SpecificStatErr=ASPS0016E: Server {0} has not received statistic {1} from server {2} since {3}, where time of reporting is {4}
Message.Explanation: A specific statistic has not arrived as expected.
Message.UserResponse: Review the core group states in the administrative console.

Message.MsgText: APMI_UP2=ASPS0013I: The statistics for the product are being gathered.
Message.Explanation: This message is for informational purposes only.

Message.MsgText: APMI_UP1=ASPS0012I: The statistics of other middleware servers that are managed by the product are being gathered.
Message.Explanation: This message is for informational purposes only.
